ExpressionSetDefinitionVersion.name: ExpressionSetDefinitionVersion
ExpressionSetDefinitionVersion.description: Represents information about an expression set definition version.

DeveloperName.description: The developer name of the expression set definition version.

ExpressionSetDefinitionId.description: The expression set definition record associated with this expression set definition version.

FullName.description: Full name of the associated metadata type in Metadata API. Query this field only if the query result contains no more than one record. Otherwise, an error is returned. If more than one record exists, use multiple queries to retrieve the records. This limit protects performance.

Language.description: The language in which this expression set definition version is created.

ManageableState.description: Indicates the manageable state of the specified component that is contained in a package.

MasterLabel.description: The label of the expression set definition version.

NamespacePrefix.description: The namespace prefix associated with this object. Each Developer Edition org that creates a managed package has a unique namespace prefix.

Status.description: Indicates the status of the expression set definition version.

VersionNumber.description: The version number of the expression set definition version. This is a required field.
